snippet: The U.N. Security Council on Wednesday blacklisted two branches of the Islamist extremist group Ansar al-Sharia in Libya, which Washington says was behind the 2012 Benghazi attack that killed the U.S. ambassador and three other Americans....

headline.print_headline: U.N. Blacklists Libya's Ansar Al-Sharia, Involved in Benghazi Attack
headline.main: U.N. Blacklists Libya's Ansar Al-Sharia, Involved in Benghazi Attack

lead_paragraph: The U.N. Security Council on Wednesday blacklisted two branches of the Islamist extremist group Ansar al-Sharia in Libya, which Washington says was behind the 2012 Benghazi attack that killed the U.S. ambassador and three other Americans.
